checkElementsNotNull

@FullyTested
public static <TValue,TIterable extends Iterable<TValue>> TIterable checkElementsNotNull(TIterable ref,
                                                                                                     String argName)
Tests if a Iterable reference is not null and each element is not null. An empty iterable will pass this test.

Parameters:
ref - an iterable reference
argName - argument name for ref, e.g., "strList" or "searchRegex"
Returns:
the validated iterable reference
Throws:
NullPointerException - if ref (or any element) is null
See Also:
ObjectArgs.checkNotNull(Object, String), ArrayArgs.checkElementsNotNull(Object[], String), CollectionArgs.checkElementsNotNull(Collection, String)
